To say 2022 has been a rollercoaster of a year would be an understatement. 
This year started off with the news of my daughter being pregnant. Sadly, she miscarried shortly after. Followed by the news that my son would be having his rainbow baby. Sharing that news with my daughter was nothing short of bittersweet. She handled it so gracefully and happily while completely broken with her own loss. 
Giving my dad the news of Alex’s rainbow baby and then losing him. My life as I knew it, would never be the same. It truly hits different when the person that loved you most in this world is no longer in it. Learning to live with someone you’ve never lived without is the hardest and saddest journey we must learn to navigate in life. 
While still grieving my father’s loss, our hearts overflowed with love and happiness when we welcomed my granddaughter, Kylie, to this earth. A beautiful reminder that there is always something to be grateful for. 
In short, and although cliché, life is short and tomorrow is never promised. Living with fear is not living at all. Regret is heavy. Time is truly the most valuable gift we can give and receive. 
I wish I could leave the pain as easily as we leave a year behind. But, in reality, I will gracefully carry it and continue to learn from it. Letting it make me softer yet stronger. 
Last but definitely not least, thank you. Thank you for supporting this dream of mine. I’ve said it once and I’ll say it again, Wee Love is not only my passion, it is also my daily therapy. I am so very grateful for all of you. 
I’m stepping into 2023 with a prayer for all those who had a rough year. May the New Year bring you peace, healing and health. May you continue to make endless memories with those that love and value you. If this holiday season was less than magical for you, I pray that in the New Year you find that spark and make it the best year ever. And may God bless each and every one of you. Happy New Years! #2023

#happynewyear #newyearblessings #missingmydad #alwaysmissingjax #everythingthatglittersisntgold #makingmemories #holidays #grateful #vacationmode
